column1: #Text=It was elevated to town status in 2009 .
#Text=This article includes travel-related information not only for Pacsa , but also for the surrounding rural areas .
#Text=The closest railway station is Zalaszentmihály-Pacsa , where you can transfer to regional buses towards Pacsa .
#Text=There are no direct trains from Budapest -Déli pályaudvar , you have to transfer in Zalaszentiván .
#Text=The whole journey from Budapest to Pacsa takes 5 hours and costs 4805 Ft.
#Text=There is no ticket office , tickets can be purchased on the train .
#Text=Direct buses from Budapest -Déli pályaudvar are available once a day , which are operated by G-Busline Kft .
#Text=The journey takes 2½ hours and costs 4015 Ft. More frequent buses are available from Zalaegerszeg .
#Text=The journey takes about 45 minutes and costs 560 Ft.
#Text=There is no local public transport or taxi service .
#Text=You can use the regional buses operated by ÉNYKK .
